{"enabled": true, "name": "Client Handover", "description": "Generate professional client-facing IPA documentation using section-segmented architecture with specialized subagents (SEQUENTIAL execution for reliability). CRITICAL: Subagents extract REAL data from source files (ANA-050 spec for business requirements, LPD Start node for configuration variables, LPD activities for workflow). Template handles both old and new workflow formats. Subagents save files directly using fsWrite. Creates comprehensive Excel report with workflow diagrams, business requirements, activity guides, and maintenance instructions. NO code criticism - focuses on how to understand and maintain the IPAs. Scalable to any IPA size. Production-grade: 95% ready (extracts truth, not AI-generated content). MULTI-PROCESS SUPPORT: Handles 1-N LPD files per RICE item, generates ONE report with separate sheets per process.", "version": "42", "when": {"type": "userTriggered"}, "newSession": true, "then": {"type": "askAgent", "prompt": "IMPORTANT: This is a HOOK-TRIGGERED workflow, NOT a spec creation request. Do NOT route this through spec creation. Do NOT ask about feature vs bugfix. Do NOT ask about requirements vs design. Execute the workflow below DIRECTLY by starting with Step 1 (user selection).\n\nIPA Client Handover Documentation - Section-Segmented Architecture\n\nThis is CLIENT-FACING documentation, NOT an internal code review.\n\nв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђ\nARCHITECTURE: Section-Segmented Documentation\nв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђ\n\nSolution: Multi-pass documentation generation\n- Python extracts and organizes data by documentation sections (5 sections)\n- AI analyzes each section with specialized subagents (SEQUENTIAL for reliability)\n- Python merges results into master documentation\n- ONE Excel report generated PER RICE ITEM (not per LPD)\n\nSections:\n1. Business Requirements - What and why (from functional spec)\n2. Workflow - How it flows (from LPD activities)\n3. Configuration - What can be changed (from config variables)\n4. Activity Guide - Reference documentation (from activities)\n5. Validation - Production proof (from WU logs)\n\nPython Role: Extract, organize, merge, format\nAI Role: Analyze sections, create client-friendly documentation\n\nв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђ\nMULTI-PROCESS SUPPORT (NEW)\nв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђ\n\nCLIENT PERSPECTIVE: One RICE item = One handover document\n- Client doesn't care how many IPAs we created internally\n- They care about the RICE deliverable as a whole\n\nREPORT STRUCTURE:\n- Executive Summary (consolidated across all processes)\n- Business Requirements (RICE-level, from spec)\n- Validation Summary (consolidated)\n- Configuration Guide (consolidated)\n- Activity Guide (consolidated)\n- Process_<ProcessName1> (detailed workflow for Process 1)\n- Process_<ProcessName2> (detailed workflow for Process 2)\n- Process_<ProcessName3> (detailed workflow for Process 3)\n- Maintenance Guide (consolidated)\n\nBACKWARD COMPATIBILITY:\n- Single LPD: Works exactly as before\n- Multiple LPDs: Consolidated into ONE report\n\nв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђ\nWORKFLOW - FOLLOW EXACTLY\nв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђ\n\nSTEP 0: CLEAN TEMP FOLDER (AUTOMATIC - NO USER PROMPT)\n\nExecute PowerShell command to wipe Temp folder:\nRemove-Item Temp/* -Recurse -Force -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue\n\nThis ensures clean slate and prevents IDE indexing issues from accumulated files.\n\nMonitor workspace size:\n$tempFiles = (Get-ChildItem Temp -File -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Measure-Object).Count\n$tempSize = [math]::Round((Get-ChildItem Temp -File -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Measure-Object -Property Length -Sum).Sum / 1MB, 2)\n\nShow: \"рџ“Љ Workspace Status: Temp has $tempFiles files ($tempSize MB)\"\n\nIf ($tempFiles -gt 50 -or $tempSize -gt 100) {\n    Show warning: \"вљ пёЏ Temp folder is large despite cleanup.\"\n}\n\nSTEP 1-5: USER SELECTION (Interactive)\n   1. List clients in Projects/ в†’ User selects\n   2. List RICE items в†’ User selects\n   3. List *.lpd files в†’ User selects ALL (multi-select with checkboxes)\n   4. Check for *.docx (spec) and *_log.txt (WU log)\n   5. Confirm selection в†’ User confirms\n   \n   IMPORTANT: Step 3 now allows selecting MULTIPLE LPD files\n   - Show checkboxes for each LPD file\n   - User can select 1 or more files\n   - All selected files will be processed into ONE report\n\nSTEP 6-10: PROCESS EACH LPD (Automated Loop)\n   \n   FOR EACH selected LPD file:\n   \n   STEP 6: EXTRACT DATA (Python)\n      \n      # Extract LPD data\n      executePwsh(\"python -c \\\"from ReusableTools.IPA_Analyzer.extract_lpd_data import extract_lpd_data; extract_lpd_data(['<lpd_path>'], 'Temp/<ProcessName>_lpd_data.json')\\\"\")\n      \n      # Extract spec data (if available and first iteration)\n      If spec file exists AND first LPD:\n          executePwsh(\"python -c \\\"from ReusableTools.IPA_Analyzer.extract_spec import extract_spec; extract_spec('<spec_path>', 'Temp/<RICEItem>_spec_data.json')\\\"\")\n      \n      # Extract WU log data (if available)\n      If WU log exists for this process:\n          executePwsh(\"python -c \\\"from ReusableTools.IPA_Analyzer.extract_wu_log import extract_wu_log; extract_wu_log('<wu_log_path>', 'Temp/<ProcessName>_wu_data.json')\\\"\")\n      \n      Verify: executePwsh(\"Test-Path Temp/<ProcessName>_lpd_data.json\")\n   \n   STEP 7: ORGANIZE BY SECTIONS (Python)\n      \n      executePwsh(\"python ReusableTools/IPA_ClientHandover/organize_by_sections.py Temp/<ProcessName>_lpd_data.json <spec_json_or_none> <wu_json_or_none> Temp/<ProcessName>\")\n      \n      Creates 5 section files:\n      - Temp/<ProcessName>_section_business.json\n      - Temp/<ProcessName>_section_workflow.json\n      - Temp/<ProcessName>_section_configuration.json\n      - Temp/<ProcessName>_section_activities.json\n      - Temp/<ProcessName>_section_validation.json\n   \n   STEP 8: LAUNCH SECTION ANALYZERS (SEQUENTIAL EXECUTION)\n      \n      Show: \"в†’ Step 8/14: Launching 5 analyzers sequentially for <ProcessName>...\"\n      \n      ANALYZER 1/5: Business Requirements\n      \n      Show: \"в†’ Analyzer 1/5: Business requirements for <ProcessName>...\"\n      \n      invokeSubAgent(\n          name=\"ipa-business-requirements-analyzer\",\n          prompt=\"STEP 1: Read spec data and section data\nreadFile('Temp/<RICEItem>_spec_data.json')\nreadFile('Temp/<ProcessName>_section_business.json')\n\nSTEP 2: Extract business requirements from ANA-050 spec\nUse spec sections (Overview, Requirements Details, Proposed Solution, Field Mapping) to create requirements.\nExtract stakeholders from spec reviewers/approvers.\nDefine scope from spec content.\n\nSTEP 3: Save analysis using chunked writes if large:\n\nIf output > 1000 lines: Use fsWrite for first 500 lines, then fsAppend for remaining chunks.\nOtherwise: Use fsWrite normally.\nSave your analysis to 'Temp/<ProcessName>_doc_business.json' using fsWrite().\",\n          explanation=\"Analyzing business requirements for <ProcessName>\"\n      )\n      \n      Show: \"вњ“ Analyzer 1/5 complete: Business requirements\"\n      \n      ANALYZER 2/5: Workflow\n      \n      Show: \"в†’ Analyzer 2/5: Workflow for <ProcessName>...\"\n      \n      invokeSubAgent(\n          name=\"ipa-workflow-analyzer\",\n          prompt=\"STEP 1: Read section data\nreadFile('Temp/<ProcessName>_section_workflow.json')\n\nSTEP 2: Map process workflow and approval paths\nCreate workflow_steps, approval_paths, and decision_points.\n\nSTEP 3: Save analysis using chunked writes if large:\n\nIf output > 1000 lines: Use fsWrite for first 500 lines, then fsAppend for remaining chunks.\nOtherwise: Use fsWrite normally.\nSave your analysis to 'Temp/<ProcessName>_doc_workflow.json' using fsWrite().\",\n          explanation=\"Analyzing workflow for <ProcessName>\"\n      )\n      \n      Show: \"вњ“ Analyzer 2/5 complete: Workflow\"\n      \n      ANALYZER 3/5: Configuration\n      \n      Show: \"в†’ Analyzer 3/5: Configuration for <ProcessName>...\"\n      \n      invokeSubAgent(\n          name=\"ipa-configuration-analyzer\",\n          prompt=\"STEP 1: Read LPD data and section data\nreadFile('Temp/<ProcessName>_lpd_data.json')\nreadFile('Temp/<ProcessName>_section_configuration.json')\n\nSTEP 2: Extract ACTUAL variables from Start node\nNavigate to processes[0]['activities'], find Start node, extract properties.\nCategorize: System Configuration (_configuration.*), File Channel (FileChannel*), Process Variables (others).\nDocument each with name, type, location, description, current value, how to modify.\n\nSTEP 3: Save analysis using chunked writes if large:\n\nIf output > 1000 lines: Use fsWrite for first 500 lines, then fsAppend for remaining chunks.\nOtherwise: Use fsWrite normally.\nSave your analysis to 'Temp/<ProcessName>_doc_configuration.json' using fsWrite().\",\n          explanation=\"Analyzing configuration for <ProcessName>\"\n      )\n      \n      Show: \"вњ“ Analyzer 3/5 complete: Configuration\"\n      \n      ANALYZER 4/5: Activity Guide\n      \n      Show: \"в†’ Analyzer 4/5: Activity guide for <ProcessName>...\"\n      \n      invokeSubAgent(\n          name=\"ipa-activity-guide-generator\",\n          prompt=\"STEP 1: Read section data\nreadFile('Temp/<ProcessName>_section_activities.json')\n\nSTEP 2: Create activity reference documentation in business terms\nCreate activities array and activity_groups.\n\nSTEP 3: Save analysis using chunked writes if large:\n\nIf output > 1000 lines: Use fsWrite for first 500 lines, then fsAppend for remaining chunks.\nOtherwise: Use fsWrite normally.\nSave your analysis to 'Temp/<ProcessName>_doc_activities.json' using fsWrite().\",\n          explanation=\"Generating activity guide for <ProcessName>\"\n      )\n      \n      Show: \"вњ“ Analyzer 4/5 complete: Activity guide\"\n      \n      ANALYZER 5/5: Validation\n      \n      Show: \"в†’ Analyzer 5/5: Validation for <ProcessName>...\"\n      \n      invokeSubAgent(\n          name=\"ipa-validation-analyzer\",\n          prompt=\"STEP 1: Read section data\nreadFile('Temp/<ProcessName>_section_validation.json')\n\nSTEP 2: Analyze work unit logs for production validation\nCreate test_summary, performance, and production_readiness.\n\nSTEP 3: Save analysis using chunked writes if large:\n\nIf output > 1000 lines: Use fsWrite for first 500 lines, then fsAppend for remaining chunks.\nOtherwise: Use fsWrite normally.\nSave your analysis to 'Temp/<ProcessName>_doc_validation.json' using fsWrite().\",\n          explanation=\"Analyzing validation data for <ProcessName>\"\n      )\n      \n      Show: \"вњ“ Analyzer 5/5 complete: Validation\"\n      Show: \"вњ“ All 5 analyzers complete for <ProcessName>\"\n      \n      IMPORTANT: Sequential execution prevents resource exhaustion.\n      Each subagent saves its own output file directly using fsWrite().\n      Subagents load their own steering files as needed.\n   \n   STEP 9: VERIFY SUBAGENT OUTPUTS\n      \n      CRITICAL: DO NOT READ SUBAGENT OUTPUTS - Python merges all data automatically\n      \n      Verify all files were saved by subagents (Test-Path only, DO NOT READ):\n      executePwsh(\"Test-Path Temp/<ProcessName>_doc_business.json\")\n      executePwsh(\"Test-Path Temp/<ProcessName>_doc_workflow.json\")\n      executePwsh(\"Test-Path Temp/<ProcessName>_doc_configuration.json\")\n      executePwsh(\"Test-Path Temp/<ProcessName>_doc_activities.json\")\n      executePwsh(\"Test-Path Temp/<ProcessName>_doc_validation.json\")\n      \n      If any file is missing, STOP and report error.\n      DO NOT READ the files - they will be merged by Python in Step 10.\n   \n   STEP 10: MERGE DOCUMENTATION FOR THIS PROCESS (Python)\n      \n      executePwsh(\"python ReusableTools/IPA_ClientHandover/merge_documentation.py Temp/<ProcessName>\")\n      \n      Creates: Temp/<ProcessName>_master_documentation.json\n   \n   END FOR EACH\n   \n   Show progress: \"вњ“ Processed <N> of <Total> LPD files\"\n\nSTEP 11: CONSOLIDATE ALL PROCESSES (Python)\n   \n   executePwsh(\"python ReusableTools/IPA_ClientHandover/consolidate_processes.py Temp/<RICEItem> <ProcessName1> <ProcessName2> ...\")\n   \n   Creates: Temp/<RICEItem>_consolidated_documentation.json\n   \n   This file contains:\n   - Consolidated business requirements (from spec - RICE level)\n   - Consolidated validation (aggregate metrics)\n   - Array of process documentation (one per LPD)\n   - Consolidated configuration guide\n   - Consolidated activity guide\n\nSTEP 12: CONFIRM REPORT GENERATION (AI)\n   \n   CRITICAL: DO NOT READ CONSOLIDATED DOCUMENTATION - Python tool handles all data loading\n   \n   Show summary of what was processed:\n   - Client: <Client>\n   - RICE Item: <RICE>\n   - Processes: <ProcessName1>, <ProcessName2>, ...\n   - Documentation sections: Business Requirements, Workflow, Configuration, Activities, Validation\n   \n   Ask: \"Generate client handover report with this documentation?\"\n   WAIT for user confirmation\n   \n   NOTE: The generate_client_handover_report.py tool will:\n   - Load consolidated documentation automatically\n   - Build ipa_data structure\n   - Call template with proper format\n   - Handle all data processing\n\nSTEP 13: GENERATE REPORT (Python - Using Reusable Tool)\n   \n   executePwsh(\"python ReusableTools/IPA_ClientHandover/generate_client_handover_report.py <RICEItem> <Client> <RICE>\")\n   \n   This tool automatically:\n   - Loads consolidated documentation\n   - Verifies all process data exists\n   - Builds correct ipa_data structure\n   - Calls template with proper format\n   - Handles errors gracefully\n   - Creates ONE report with separate sheets per process\n   \n   Verify: executePwsh(\"Test-Path Client_Handover_Results/<Client>_<RICE>_*.xlsx\")\n\nSTEP 13.5: CLEANUP OLD RESULT FILES (Optional)\n   \n   Check result folder sizes:\n   $codingCount = (Get-ChildItem Coding_Standards_Results -File | Measure-Object).Count\n   $handoverCount = (Get-ChildItem Client_Handover_Results -File | Measure-Object).Count\n   $perfCount = (Get-ChildItem Performance_Results -File | Measure-Object).Count\n   $totalResults = $codingCount + $handoverCount + $perfCount\n   \n   If $totalResults > 20:\n       Show: \"рџ“Љ Result folders have $totalResults reports total\"\n       \n       userInput(\n           question=\"рџ§№ Archive old reports? (Moves reports older than 30 days to Archive/)\",\n           options=[\"Yes, archive old reports\", \"No, keep everything\"],\n           reason=\"general-question\"\n       )\n       \n       If user selects \"Yes, archive old reports\":\n           # Create Archive folders\n           executePwsh(\"New-Item -ItemType Directory -Force -Path Archive/Coding_Standards, Archive/Client_Handover, Archive/Performance | Out-Null\")\n           \n           # Move old files (>30 days)\n           executePwsh(\"$oldFiles = Get-ChildItem Coding_Standards_Results, Client_Handover_Results, Performance_Results -File | Where-Object { $_.LastWriteTime -lt (Get-Date).AddDays(-30) }; $oldCount = ($oldFiles | Measure-Object).Count; foreach ($file in $oldFiles) { $dest = $file.DirectoryName -replace '_Results', ''; Move-Item $file.FullName -Destination \\\"Archive/$dest/\\\" -Force }; Write-Output \\\"вњ“ Archived $oldCount old reports\\\"\"\n           \n           # Show current counts\n           executePwsh(\"$currentCount = (Get-ChildItem Coding_Standards_Results, Client_Handover_Results, Performance_Results -File | Measure-Object).Count; Write-Output \\\"вњ“ $currentCount recent reports remain\\\"\")\n\nSTEP 14: DONE\n   \n   Show summary:\n   вњ“ Report generated: <filename>\n   вњ“ Processes documented: <N>\n   вњ“ Client-facing documentation complete\n\nв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђ\nCRITICAL RULES\nв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђ\n\n1. ONE REPORT PER RICE ITEM (NEW)\n   - N LPDs в†’ ONE report\n   - Each process gets its own sheet: Process_<ProcessName>\n   - Executive summary consolidates across all processes\n   - Backward compatible: 1 LPD works exactly as before\n\n2. SECTION-SEGMENTED ANALYSIS WITH SUBAGENTS (SEQUENTIAL)\n   - Launch 5 specialized subagents ONE AT A TIME (Step 8)\n   - Sequential execution prevents resource exhaustion and cancellations\n   - Each subagent completes before next one starts\n   - Subagents save files directly using fsWrite (Step 8)\n   - Subagents load their own steering files (no duplicate loading by main agent)\n\n3. CLIENT-FACING LANGUAGE ONLY\n   - NO code criticism or technical details\n   - Focus on WHAT and WHY, not HOW\n   - Use business language, not technical jargon\n   - Explain how to maintain, not how to fix\n\n4. PYTHON LIFTS HEAVY LOAD\n   - Python: Extract, organize, merge, format\n   - AI: Analyze sections, create documentation\n   - Python does NOT make judgments\n\n5. ONE EXCEL REPORT PER RICE ITEM\n   - Multi-pass analysis в†’ ONE consolidated documentation file\n   - ONE Excel report per RICE item (not per LPD)\n   - Variable number of sheets based on process count\n   - 8+ sheets: Executive, Business, Validation, Config, Activities, Process_1, Process_2, ..., Maintenance\n\n6. ERROR HANDLING\n   - If ANY step fails: STOP, show error, offer retry\n   - Verify files exist before proceeding (Test-Path)\n   - Show documentation summary BEFORE generating report\n\n7. GRACEFUL DEGRADATION\n   - If no spec: Infer requirements from LPD\n   - If no WU log: Note validation not available\n   - Report still generates with available data\n\nCONFIDENTIALITY: Client-facing documentation. Do not reference other clients.\n\nPERFORMANCE:\n- Extraction: ~1s per file\n- Organization: ~2s per process\n- AI analysis (5 subagents sequential): ~2-3 min per process\n- Consolidation: ~2s\n- Report generation: <10s\n- Total: ~2-3 min per process + consolidation\n\nSUBAGENTS:\n- ipa-business-requirements-analyzer: Business requirements from spec\n- ipa-workflow-analyzer: Process flow and approval paths\n- ipa-configuration-analyzer: Configuration guide with modification instructions\n- ipa-activity-guide-generator: Activity reference documentation\n- ipa-validation-analyzer: Production validation from WU logs\n\nAll subagents located in .kiro/agents/ with read and fsWrite tools. Subagents save files directly."}}